{"data":[{"name":"101:1","price":"वह खड़खड़ा देने वाली।","arabic":"ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6158,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"al-qāriʿatu ","translations":["The Striking Calamity","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["al-qāriʿatu",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2245]]}},{"name":"101:2","price":"क्या है वह खड़खड़ा देने वाली?","arabic":"مَا ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6159,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"mā al-qāriʿatu ","translations":["What","(is) the Striking Calamity","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["mā","al-qāriʿatu",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,240],[2,240,2215]]}},{"name":"101:3","price":"और तुम क्या जानो कि वह खड़खड़ा देने वाली क्या है?[1]","arabic":"وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6160,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"1. 'क़ारिअह' प्रलय ही का एक नाम है जो उसके समय की घोर दशा का चित्रण करता है। इसका शाब्दिक अर्थ द्वार खटखटाना है। जब कोई अतिथि अकस्मात रात में आता है तो उसे दरवाज़ा खटखटाने की आवश्यकता होती है। जिससे एक तो यह ज्ञात हुआ कि प्रलय अकस्मात होगी। और दूसरा यह ज्ञात हुआ कि वह कड़ी ध्वनि और भारी उथल-पुथल के साथ आएगी। इसे प्रश्नवाचक वाक्यों में दोहराना सावधान करने और उसकी गंभीरता को प्रस्तुत करने के लिए है।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā adrāka mā al-qāriʿatu ","translations":["And what","will make you know","what","(is) the Striking Calamity","(3)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","adrāka","mā","al-qāriʿatu",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2189],[2,2189,3639],[3,3639,3759],[4,3759,5464]]}},{"name":"101:4","price":"जिस दिन लोग बिखरे हुए पतिंगों की तरह हो जाएँगे।","arabic":"يَوۡمَ يَكُونُ ٱلنَّاسُ كَٱلۡفَرَاشِ ٱلۡمَبۡثُوثِ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6161,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"yawma yakūnu al-nāsu kal-farāshi al-mabthūthi ","translations":["(The) Day","will be","the mankind","like moths","scattered","(4)"],"transliterationArr":["yawma","yakūnu","al-nāsu","kal-farāshi","al-mabthūthi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,680],[2,680,1580],[3,1580,3150],[4,3150,4470],[5,4470,7355]]}},{"name":"101:5","price":"और पर्वत धुने हुए रंगीन ऊन की तरह हो जाएँगे।[2]","arabic":"وَتَكُونُ ٱلۡجِبَالُ كَٱلۡعِهۡنِ ٱلۡمَنفُوشِ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6162,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"2. (4-5) इन दोनों आयतों में उस स्थिति को दर्शाया गया है जो उस समय लोगों और पर्वतों की होगी।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"watakūnu al-jibālu kal-ʿih'ni al-manfūshi ","translations":["And will be","the mountains","like wool","fluffed up","(5)"],"transliterationArr":["watakūnu","al-jibālu","kal-ʿih'ni","al-manfūshi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1120],[2,1120,2270],[3,2270,3360],[4,3360,7535]]}},{"name":"101:6","price":"तो जिसके पलड़े भारी हो गए,","arabic":"فَأَمَّا مَن ثَقُلَتۡ مَوَٰزِينُهُۥ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6163,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fa-ammā man thaqulat mawāzīnuhu ","translations":["Then as for","(him) whose","(are) heavy","his scales","(6)"],"transliterationArr":["fa-ammā","man","thaqulat","mawāzīnuhu",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2000],[2,2000,2970],[3,2970,3900],[4,3900,5655]]}},{"name":"101:7","price":"तो वह संतोषजनक जीवन में होगा।","arabic":"فَهُوَ فِي عِيشَةٖ رَّاضِيَةٖ","category":["101 (Al-Qari'ah)","Al-Qari'ah","Surah Al-Qari'ah"],"ayahNumber":6164,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fahuwa fī ʿīshatin rāḍiyatin ","translations":["Then he","(will be) in","a life","pleasant","(7)"],"transliterationArr":["fahuwa","fī","ʿīshatin","rāḍiyatin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,610],[2,610,1160],[3,1160,2240],[4,2240,3785]]}},{"name":"101:8","price":"तथा जिसके पलड़े हल्के हो गए,","arabic":"وَأَمَّا مَنۡ خَفَّتۡ مَوَٰزِين